  "prompt": "Does the warranty on the car electrical wiring lapse in case one gets a music system fitted from outside and not from the company showroom?",
  "response": "The impact on the car's warranty for electrical wiring depends on several factors:\n\n1. Installation Quality:\n- If the music system is professionally installed without damaging the original electrical wiring\n- If high-quality wiring and professional installation techniques are used\n- If no original electrical systems are modified or tampered with\n\n2. Manufacturer's Policy:\n- Different car manufacturers have varying warranty policies\n- Some manufacturers might void warranty if aftermarket accessories are installed\n- Others may allow modifications without affecting warranty\n\n3. Potential Warranty Implications:\n- If improper installation causes electrical damage\n- If new wiring interferes with original electrical systems\n- If modifications lead to electrical system failures\n\n4. Recommended Steps:\n- Consult the car manufacturer's warranty terms\n- Use authorized/recommended installation services\n- Keep original installation receipts and documentation\n- Inform the dealership about the aftermarket music system installation\n\n5. Best Practice:\n- If possible, get the music system installed through the authorized dealer\n- Use certified technicians who understand the car's electrical system\n- Ensure minimal interference with original wiring\n\nSpecific details can vary, so it's best to directly check with your car manufacturer or dealership for precise information about your specific vehicle's warranty conditions.",
